cs.DB, cs.DS, cs.OS, cs.PF, cs.AR 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of databases (cs.DB) because it presents a new index structure for in-memory databases. It is also likely to belong to the data structures (cs.DS) and operating systems (cs.OS) sub-categories because it discusses the efficiency of index structures in the context of multi-core architectures and non-uniform memory access. Additionally, it may belong to the performance (cs.PF) and architecture (cs.AR) sub-categories because it presents a new index structure that is designed to be efficient in a parallel and concurrent environment.
